I apologies for not releasing a final or normal compiled map without any glitches. This is my first map, attempting to create a master piece while I was learning the ropes. I am very disappointed with how it came out but decided it will still be a nice contribution for those slide fans.

Contents of This Pack:
==================
This pack contains the exact same maps as my "Orange Arena Map Pack One" collection, but with real textures, for those who don't like orange maps.

Orange Arena Pack One: http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/178481

Important part:
===============

This time, the maps for some reason had an issue with the Navigation Mesh (The thing that lets bots know where they can and can't go) so I had to edit it.
When placing the .bsp files into your maps folder, please also place the .nav files, or else bots will be useless.

The main issue was with the Terrorist's spawn on cs_Alley where they couldn't get out of spawn. There wasn't a notable problem with cs_Metropolis, but I included it for safe measures. If you do not, Terrorists on cs_Alley will be stuck in their spawn and not be able to get out.

**I give you permission to download these maps and use them on your server/suggest them to other servers without consulting me.
_However,_ I do not give you permission to re-upload, with or without altering, without consulting me first.**

Installation instructions:
==========================

Drag and drop the .bsp and .nav files into your Counter Strike maps folder.

Possible folder locations:

C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\SteamApps\common\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps

C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\common\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps

If you installed CS:S onto your main/internal hard drive, it should be in one of those locations unless you selected an alternate install location.
________________________________________________________

Many thanks,
**(Lemon) WUNDerDUDe2312**

I designed this map for a 1vs1 knife tournament which will be held on our server. (I will change a few things for that tournament.)

So this map is small! I wouldn't recommend more them 10 players on this map. But made it with 24 spawns anyways.

It is modelled after Mortal Kombat's Kuatan Palace arena. It is not a perfect copy though, I just tried to make it look like that.

Map has no problems as it is but still has a lot of room for improvement :) Maybe a bigger version or something..

---

Music, "fight" voice, original map design and mortal kombat logo belongs to the [NetherRealm Studios](http://www.netherrealm.com/ "nether realm")' [Mortal Kombat](http://www.mortalkombat.com/ "Mortal Kombat") ([Kuatan Palace](http://mortalkombat.wikia.com/wiki/Kuatan_Palace "Kuatan Palace").)

[Countdown voice](https://www.freesound.org/people/Corsica_S/sounds/82986/ "Countdown Voice") by [Corsica_S / Amy Gedgaudas](https://www.freesound.org/people/Corsica_S/ "Corsica S") is licensed under [CC BY 3.0](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/ "CC BY 3.0")

There is an open arena and a tunnel. You can use teleportation for going between these two.

There is a catapult (I couldn't find any other way to describe it :D) which is synced with its counter part. When first player enters, it waits five seconds for someone else to enter the one at the opposite side, if someone enters in 5 seconds they are immediately launched meeting at the center. After 5 seconds if nobody enters the other catapult, you launch alone.

Roofs of the shacks in the middle pushes people so people can't wait on them. Because of this you can jump long distances and land on enemy players.

The top side path doubles the speed of the players. There are hazard markers on the ground to see when the speed is activated and disabled.

There is a teleporter from the water to the top side path.

Inside the tunnel you have 2x speed and flickering lights. When you reach the other side of the tunnel you come out from the enemy base.

One of the shacks has a suprise from HL2 :)) and the tunnel has one from Batman.

Hope you like it, sinsic.
